The API is a protocol for interaction between your software and our activation service. This is necessary to automate the SMS receiving process on your side.
All requests (GET only) must go to this address:

https://api.smsfast.com/stubs/handler_api.php

Possible errors (Activation)

Server response	Description
BAD_KEY	Invalid API-key
ERROR_SQL	SQL Server error
BAD_ACTION	Incorrect request formation
NO_NUMBERS	There are no numbers with the specified parameters, try again later, or change the operator, country
NO_BALANCE	Account funds have run out
BAD_SERVICE	Invalid service ID
NO_ACTIVATION	The activation ID does not exist
Possible errors (Rent)

Server response	Description
BAD_KEY	Invalid API key
NO_ID_RENT	Rent ID not specified
INVALID_PHONE	The number was not rented by you (incorrect rent ID)
INCORECT_STATUS	Missing or incorrectly specified status
CANT_CANCEL	Unable to cancel rent (more than 15 minutes have passed)
ALREADY_FINISH	Rent already completed
ALREADY_CANCEL	Rent already cancelled
SERVER_ERROR	Server error
MAX_HOURS_EXCEED	Maximum allowed time exceeded
RENT_DIE	Rent cannot be extended as the number’s lifetime has expired
NO_BALANCE	Insufficient account balance
CHANNELS_LIMIT	Account channel limit reached (account is blocked)
WRONG_COUNTRY	Incorrect country ID specified
INVALID_TIME	Incorrect time specified
Activation API
Ordering a phone number
This request is intended to receive a virtual number. It allows you to set parameters such as service, carrier, and country to get a number for later use.

https://api.smsfast.com/stubs/handler_api.php?api_key=APIKEY&action=getNumber&service=SERVICE&operator=OPERATOR&country=COUNTRY

Input parameters

Parameter	The values that this parameter accepts	Obligatory	Description
APIKEY	See in the account settings	Yes	The API key provides access to paid services.
SERVICE	See the list of services in the left menu	Yes	The service for which you need to receive a number
OPERATOR	See the list of operators in the left menu.	No	The mobile operator whose number you need to get
COUNTRY	See the list of countries in the left menu.	Yes	The country whose number you need to get
URL	Full webhook URL (http/https)	No	Webhook endpoint. If set, we POST SMS data to this URL when an SMS arrives for the purchased number.
MAXPRICE	Number (integer or decimal with a dot)	No	If the number being purchased costs more than the passed parameter, NO_NUMBERS will be returned even if numbers are available.
The service's response

The service's response	Example	Description
ACCESS_NUMBER:ID:NUMBER	ACCESS_NUMBER:234242:79123456789	We received a number, an activation ID, and the number itself with the country code is a NUMBER
Change the status
This request is used to manage the status of the number in the system.

https://api.smsfast.com/stubs/handler_api.php?api_key=APIKEY&action=setStatus&status=STATUS&id=ID

Input parameters

Parameter	The values that this parameter accepts	Obligatory	Description
APIKEY	See in the account settings	Yes	The API key provides access to paid services.
ID	Numeric value	Yes	Activation ID received when requesting a number
STATUS	Numeric value	Yes	The status that needs to be transferred to the number
Supported status values:

3 - SMS resend requested

6 - activation successfully completed

8 - activation cancelled, refund issued


The service's response

The service's response	Description
STATUS_WAIT_CODE	Waiting for an SMS message to be received
ACCESS_ACTIVATION	Activation completed successfully
ACCESS_CANCEL	Activation cancelled
Get a status
This request is used to get the status of the number in the system.

https://api.smsfast.com/stubs/handler_api.php?api_key=APIKEY&action=getStatus&id=ID

Input parameters

Parameter	The values that this parameter accepts	Obligatory	Description
APIKEY	See in the account settings	Yes	The API key provides access to paid services.
ID	Numeric value	Yes	Activation ID received when requesting a number

The service's response

The service's response	Description
STATUS_WAIT_CODE	Waiting for an SMS message to be received
STATUS_CANCEL	Activation cancelled
STATUS_OK:CODE	The received code (CODE is the activation code
Request the number of available numbers
The request is intended to get information about the available number of phone numbers.

https://api.smsfast.com/stubs/handler_api.php?api_key=APIKEY&action=getNumbersStatus&country=COUNTRY&operator=OPERATOR

Input parameters

Parameter	The values that this parameter accepts	Obligatory	Description
APIKEY	See in the account settings	Yes	The API key provides access to paid services.
COUNTRY	See the list of services in the left menu	Yes	The country of the number
OPERATOR	See the list of operators in the left menu	No	The number operator. If no parameter is specified, a random operator will be used.
The service's response

The service's response	Description
JSON response	Response in the format {"Service_0":"Quantity"}
Request all prices
This request allows you to get a list of available prices for this service and the country. It is used to get up-to-date information about the cost of services.

https://api.smsfast.com/stubs/handler_api.php?api_key=APIKEY&action=getPrices&service=SERVICE&country=COUNTRY

Input parameters

Parameter	The values that this parameter accepts	Obligatory	Description
APIKEY	See in the account settings	Yes	The API key provides access to paid services.
COUNTRY	See the list of countries in the left menu	Yes	The country of the number
SERVICE	See the list of services in the left menu	No	Necessary service
The service's response

The service's response	Description
JSON response	Response in the format {"Country":{"Price":Quanity}}}
Balance request
This request is used to get the current account balance associated with the specified API key.

https://api.smsfast.com/stubs/handler_api.php?api_key=APIKEY&action=getBalance


Input parameters

Parameter	The values that this parameter accepts	Obligatory	Description
APIKEY	See in the account settings	Yes	The API key provides access to paid services.
The service's response

The service's response	Example	Description
ACCESS_BALANCE:BALANCE	ACCESS_BALANCE:540	BALANCE - your account balance

